@REMARK -----------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Intro" "Introduction"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Introduction@{APEN 1}
@{JLEFT}
@{BODY}
@{APEN 2}
@{PAR}@{APEN 1}Requester Reboot is a small reboot utility suitable for either a shell script /
pulldown menu / start button clone / tooldock, etc..  It can be run from both
Workbench and the shell.  Please see the @{"Usage" LINK "Usage"} section.

@{APEN 2}
@{PAR}What?!?  @{B}Another@{UB} reboot utility?  @{APEN 1}Requester Reboot was born becuase it took
about 10 minutes to write.  Given that amount of time archives sit in my downloads
directory, its a far faster turn around!  Instead of just leaving it on my HD, I decided to
release it to Aminet.  If even one other person uses it, then it is worth it.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -----------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Require" "Requirments"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Requirements@{APEN 1}
@{JLEFT}
@{B}Minimum Requirements@{UB}

À OS2.0+
À Approximately 15K of HD space

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -----------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Installation@{APEN 1}
@{JLEFT}
To install ReqReboot on your system, perform the following steps:

1 - Copy the ReqReboot executable to your C: assign.

2 - (OPTIONAL) Copy this document to a safe place.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -----------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Usage" "Usage"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Usage@{APEN 1}
@{JLEFT}
ReqReboot can either either pop up a reboot requester (the default) or silently
reboot your machine.  To do this, it supports one command line argument.

@{B}WARNING@{UB}: All unsaved data will be lost!  Do not use this program lightly.

@{B}REQREBOOT@{UB} - Reboot Utility

@{APEN 2}Format      :@{APEN 1} ReqReboot [NOREQ]
@{APEN 2}Template    :@{APEN 1} N=NOREQ/S
@{APEN 2}Description :@{APEN 1}

  N=NOREQ/S - ReqReboot defaults to showing a requester (as its name suggests).
              To silently reboot your machine, set the NOREQ switch.

@ENDNODE

